Plot
Most screenwriters fight to protect their creative vision, but one 
man goes a good bit farther than most in this sequel to the 
made-for-TV horror flick Cabin by the Lake. Murderous scriptwriter 
Stanley Caldwell (Judd Nelson) is missing and thought to be dead, 
but the strange stories of his grisly crimes have made the project 
he was writing at the time of his death a hot property, and director 
Mike Helton (Brian Krause) has hired writer Allison Gaddis 
(Dahlia Salem) to polish Caldwell&#039;s rough draft as he prepares to 
bring Stanley&#039;s final work to the big screen. But it turns out 
Stanley isn&#039;t dead after all -- he managed to escape and has gone 
into hiding, but the news that his work is being tampered with 
brings him back to the scene of his crimes. Posing as J.C. Reddick, 
a relative of the producer, Caldwell gets hired as an assistant 
director on the film, and claiming to have known the late Caldwell, 
he sets out to reshape the movie so that it reflects his own twisted 
ideals. Produced for the USA cable network, Return to Cabin by the 
Lake was first aired on December 15, 2001. ~ Mark Deming, 
All Movie Guide
